<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Your mother must have been <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="quite a slave to your education; be a slave to sth - 受...控制、沉迷于、深受...的影响"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(忙于教育你们)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>If I had known your mother, I should have advised her most strenuously to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="engage"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(雇佣)</code></b> one.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I am always glad to get a young person <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="well placed out"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(被安排了好差事)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She is <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="full young to be much in company"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(还太小，不适宜多交朋友)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Mr. Collins was employed in agreeing to everything her Ladyship said, thanking her for <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="every fish he won"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(每每赢了)</code></b>, and apologizing if he thought he won too many.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Sir William did not say much. He was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="storing his memory with anecdotes and noble names"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(将这些轶事和尊贵的名字存到记忆里)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He was very soon obliged to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="take her Ladyship's praise into his own hands; take sth into one's own hands - (因为别人不能处理而)把事情接过来亲自处理"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(亲自把Catherine夫人的恭维重新赞扬了一番)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>It was a better sized room, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="had a pleasanter aspect"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(氛围更舒适)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

